%% state_03_task_application.mmd — TaskApplication Status
%% Updated 2026-05-18.
%% Ref: task_application model (application_status: pending/approved/rejected/withdrawn)
%% Constraint: UNIQUE(task_id, applicant_id) — 1 application per task per user
%% Only task creator can approve/reject applications.

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> pending : Freelancer applies\n(1-click, profile auto-attached)

    pending --> approved : Creator approves\n→ Create TaskAssignment
    pending --> rejected : Creator rejects\n(with rejection_reason)
    pending --> withdrawn : Applicant withdraws

    approved --> [*]
    rejected --> [*]
    withdrawn --> [*]

    note right of pending
        1-click apply: no form, no cover letter.
        Profile data (skills, spider chart, trust score)
        auto-attached from user_skills + users.
        ──────────────────
        Only TASK CREATOR can approve/reject.
        Approving does NOT change task status.
        Task stays in current status (e.g. todo).
        Assignee must manually start work.
    end note

    note left of approved
        On approval:
        • INSERT task_assignment (status=active)
        • SET task.assigned_to = applicant_id
        • Reject all other pending applications
        • Notify applicant
    end note
